          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ContractDelete",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to delete a contract and its associated records from a billing system. It performs a series of deletions across multiple tables related to contracts, ensuring that all associated data is removed if the contract is not linked to any invoice groups. The procedure also logs the operation's details, including any exceptions that occur during execution."
        }
